Create API test scenarios for:
DELETE /user/{id}
Include:
Valid ID
Invalid ID
Unauthorized request
Non-existent user
Solution:
| TC ID  | Test Scenario                                     | Test Data                                            | Expected Result                                                                             |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| TC_001 | Delete an existing user with a valid ID           | Valid user ID (e.g., 101)                            | Status **200 OK** or **204 No Content**. User is successfully deleted.                      |
| TC_002 | Verify the deleted user no longer exists          | Previously deleted user ID                           | GET request returns **404 Not Found** or equivalent.                                        |
| TC_003 | Delete the same user again                        | Same deleted user ID                                 | Status **404 Not Found**. Appropriate error message returned.                               |
| TC_004 | Delete a user with an invalid ID format           | `abc`, `@123`, `12#`                                 | Status **400 Bad Request**. Validation error returned.                                      |
| TC_005 | Delete a user with a negative ID                  | `-1`                                                 | Status **400 Bad Request**. Validation error returned.                                      |
| TC_006 | Delete a user with ID as zero                     | `0`                                                  | Status **400 Bad Request** or **404 Not Found**, based on API design.                       |
| TC_007 | Delete a user with a very large ID                | `999999999999`                                       | Status **404 Not Found** or validation error.                                               |
| TC_008 | Delete without providing an authentication token  | No Authorization header                              | Status **401 Unauthorized**. Authentication error returned.                                 |
| TC_009 | Delete with an expired authentication token       | Expired JWT/Token                                    | Status **401 Unauthorized**. Token expired message returned.                                |
| TC_010 | Delete with an invalid authentication token       | Random/invalid token                                 | Status **401 Unauthorized**. Invalid token message returned.                                |
| TC_011 | Delete using a user without delete permission     | Valid token with insufficient privileges             | Status **403 Forbidden**. Authorization error returned.                                     |
| TC_012 | Delete a non-existent user                        | Non-existent user ID (e.g., 999999)                  | Status **404 Not Found**. User not found message returned.                                  |
| TC_013 | Verify response headers after successful deletion | Valid user ID                                        | Correct `Content-Type`, security headers, and cache headers are present.                    |
| TC_014 | Verify response time                              | Valid user ID                                        | Response time is within SLA (e.g., < 2 seconds).                                            |
| TC_015 | Verify idempotency                                | Send DELETE request multiple times for the same ID   | First request succeeds; subsequent requests return **404 Not Found** without server errors. |
| TC_016 | Verify SQL Injection attempt in path parameter    | `/user/' OR 1=1--`                                   | Request is rejected with **400 Bad Request**. No unintended records are deleted.            |
| TC_017 | Verify XSS payload in path parameter              | `/user/<script>alert(1)</script>`                    | Input is rejected. No script execution.                                                     |
| TC_018 | Verify concurrent delete requests                 | Two DELETE requests for the same user simultaneously | One request succeeds; the other returns **404 Not Found** or another appropriate response.  |
| TC_019 | Verify deletion is reflected in related APIs      | Deleted user ID                                      | User is absent from GET/List APIs and dependent services behave correctly.                  |
| TC_020 | Verify audit logging (if applicable)              | Valid delete request                                 | Deletion event is recorded with user, timestamp, and action details.                        |
